column2: Foreign Direct Investment: % of Nominal GDP: Annual: Sri Lanka
1. CEIC calculates annual Foreign Direct Investment as % of Nominal GDP from annual Foreign Direct Investment and annual Nominal GDP.

column1: 2. The Central Bank of Sri Lanka provides Foreign Direct Investment in USD based on BPM6. The Department of Census and Statistics provides Nominal GDP in local currency based on SNA 2008. Federal Reserve Board average market exchange rate is used for currency conversions.
3. Foreign Direct Investment as % of Nominal GDP prior to 2012 is calculated from Foreign Direct Investment based on BPM5 and Nominal GDP based on SNA 1993.
